main event: Three unidentified objects were observed in the sky in Austria on August 16, 1953.
interesting points: The objects were as large as the planet Venus.
The objects were observed for 3 minutes and were described as 'VERY BRIGHT'.
The Air Force's Project Blue Book investigation concluded that the objects were possibly balloons, but the data was insufficient for a definitive evaluation.
The report does not mention any photographs being taken of the objects.
The report does not provide any additional details about the appearance, movement, or other characteristics of the objects.
